<script lang="ts">
  const html: string = "<h1>Timeline List Item</h1>\n\n<p>A timeline list item is a single entry within a TimelineList, rendered as a semantic <code>&lt;li&gt;</code> element. Each item typically contains a timestamp (via the <code>&lt;time&gt;</code> element) and a description of the event or milestone.</p>\n\n<h2>Implementation Notes</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Renders a <code>&lt;li&gt;</code> element with class <code>timeline-list-item</code></li>\n<li>Spreads <code>restProps</code> onto the root element for consumer customization</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Help</h2>\n\n<p>Use TimelineListItem for individual entries within a TimelineList. Common scenarios include project milestones, order status updates, activity feed entries, and historical events. Each item should represent a single event or point in time.</p>\n\n<h2>Syntax</h2>\n\n<pre><code class=\"language-html\">&lt;TimelineListItem&gt;\n  &lt;!-- event content --&gt;\n&lt;/TimelineListItem&gt;</code></pre>\n\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n\n<p>Timeline entry with semantic time element:</p>\n\n<pre><code class=\"language-html\">&lt;TimelineList label=\"Order history\"&gt;\n    &lt;TimelineListItem&gt;\n        &lt;time datetime=\"2024-01-15\"&gt;January 15, 2024&lt;/time&gt;\n        &lt;p&gt;Order placed&lt;/p&gt;\n    &lt;/TimelineListItem&gt;\n    &lt;TimelineListItem&gt;\n        &lt;time datetime=\"2024-01-16\"&gt;January 16, 2024&lt;/time&gt;\n        &lt;p&gt;Order shipped&lt;/p&gt;\n    &lt;/TimelineListItem&gt;\n&lt;/TimelineList&gt;</code></pre>\n\n<p>Timeline entry with status data attribute for conditional styling:</p>\n\n<pre><code class=\"language-html\">&lt;TimelineListItem data-status=\"completed\"&gt;\n    &lt;time datetime=\"2024-03-01T10:30\"&gt;10:30 AM&lt;/time&gt;\n    &lt;p&gt;User completed onboarding&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;/TimelineListItem&gt;</code></pre>\n\n<h2>Props</h2>\n\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr><th>Prop</th><th>Type</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr><td><code>children</code></td><td><code>slot</code></td><td>(required)</td><td>Content for the timeline entry</td></tr>\n<tr><td><code>...restProps</code></td><td>HTML attributes</td><td></td><td>Additional attributes spread onto the <code>&lt;li&gt;</code> element</td></tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h2>Examples</h2>\n\n<p>Activity feed item:</p>\n\n<pre><code class=\"language-html\">&lt;TimelineListItem data-status=\"completed\"&gt;\n  &lt;time datetime=\"2024-03-01T10:30\"&gt;10:30 AM&lt;/time&gt;\n  &lt;p&gt;User completed onboarding&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;/TimelineListItem&gt;</code></pre>\n\n<h2>Keyboard Interactions</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>None directly -- standard list item navigation by screen readers</li>\n<li>Tab moves focus between any interactive elements (links, buttons) within the item</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>ARIA</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Semantic <code>&lt;li&gt;</code> element within an <code>&lt;ol&gt;</code> conveys ordered list item semantics</li>\n<li>Consumers should use <code>&lt;time&gt;</code> elements with <code>datetime</code> attributes for machine-readable dates</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>When to Use</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Use inside TimelineList to represent one event or milestone with a date and description.</li>\n<li>Use when each entry represents a distinct point in time with a timestamp and description.</li>\n<li>Use for individual project milestones, order status updates, or activity feed entries.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>When Not to Use</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Do not use outside TimelineList -- it renders an <code>&lt;li&gt;</code> that requires an <code>&lt;ol&gt;</code> context.</li>\n<li>Do not use for chat messages -- use ChatMessage instead.</li>\n<li>Do not use for task items with checkboxes -- use CheckListItem or TaskListItem instead.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Headless</h2>\n\n<p>This headless component provides a semantic <code>&lt;li&gt;</code> element for a single chronological entry within an ordered list. The consumer provides all content (timestamps, descriptions, icons) and all visual styling including markers, connectors, and layout.</p>\n\n<h2>Styles</h2>\n\n<p>The consumer provides all CSS styling. The component renders with a <code>.timeline-list-item</code> class for targeting. No default styles are included — this is a fully headless component.</p>\n\n<h2>Testing</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Verify the component renders a <code>&lt;li&gt;</code> element with class <code>timeline-list-item</code></li>\n<li>Verify keyboard interactions work correctly</li>\n<li>Verify pass-through attributes are applied</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Advice</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Designers</strong>: Give each item a clear visual marker (dot, icon, or number) and a prominent timestamp to reinforce the timeline sequence.</li>\n<li><strong>Developers</strong>: Include <code>&lt;time datetime=\"...\"&gt;</code> elements for machine-readable dates. Use <code>data-*</code> attributes for status indicators that can drive conditional styling.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Composition</h2>\n\n<p>TimelineListItem is a child of TimelineList, following the List/ListItem pattern. Each TimelineListItem represents one chronological event within the parent TimelineList container.</p>\n\n<h2>Related components</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><code>timeline-list</code> — an ordered list of chronological events or milestones</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>References</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>HTML <code>&lt;li&gt;</code> element: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/li</li>\n<li>HTML <code>&lt;time&gt;</code> element: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/time</li>\n</ul>";
</script>

